Reviewed lifecycle mapping treats CREATING as
provisioning, UPDATING as updating, ACTIVE and
INACTIVE as success, and DELETING as
terminating; FAILED is terminal and DELETED is
only a delete-confirmation target.
Create, update, and delete responses expose
work-request headers but do not return a
VbInstance body. The runtime resumes through
GetWorkRequest, recovers the affected VbInstance
OCID from work-request resources, and then
rereads GetVbInstance before settling.
Pre-create reuse keeps exact compartmentId plus
displayName matching bounded to ACTIVE,
CREATING, UPDATING, or INACTIVE summaries.
In-place reconcile covers displayName,
nodeCount, freeformTags, definedTags, one-way
enablement of isVisualBuilderEnabled,
customEndpoint, alternateCustomEndpoints, and
the mutable public/private
networkEndpointDetails surface. CompartmentId,
consumptionModel, and privateEndpointIp remain
replacement-only, while idcsOpenId is
create-only because OCI does not project it back
on live reads.
ChangeVbInstanceCompartment, StartVbInstance,
StopVbInstance, and
ReconfigurePrivateEndpointVbInstance remain out
of scope for the published
create/get/list/update/delete runtime.
